!!!
%html{:lang => "en"}
  %head
    %meta{:charset => "utf-8"}
    %title SSO Login
    %meta{:content => "width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0", :name => "viewport"}
    %meta{:content => "Super Portal", :name => "description"}
    %meta{:content => "Horst Kapfenberger", :name => "author"}
    %link{:rel => "stylesheet", :href => "//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.0.0/css/bootstrap.min.css", :media => "screen"}
    %link{:rel => "stylesheet", :href => "//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.0.0/css/bootstrap-theme.min.css"}
    :css
      body {
        padding-top: 40px;
        padding-bottom: 40px;
        background-color: #f5f5f5;
        background: url('/images/bg.png');
        background-position: center top;
        background-repeat: no-repeat;
      }
      .form-signin {
        max-width: 350px;
        padding: 19px 29px 29px;
        margin: 0 auto 20px;
        background-color: #fff;
                border: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
        -webkit-border-radius: 5px;
           -moz-border-radius: 5px;
                border-radius: 5px;
        -webkit-box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,.05);
           -moz-box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,.05);
                box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,.05);
      }
      .form-signin .form-signin-heading,
        .form-signin .checkbox {
        margin-bottom: 10px;
      }
      .form-signin input[type="text"],
        .form-signin input[type="password"] {
        font-size: 16px;
        height: auto;
        margin-bottom: 15px;
        padding: 7px 9px;
      }
    %script{:src => "//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.0.0/js/bootstrap.min.js"}
    / HTML5 shim, for IE6-8 support of HTML5 elements
    /[if lt IE 9]
      <script src="js/html5shiv.js"></script>
      <script src="js/respond.min.js"></script>
      <script src="js/ie-hacks.js"></script>
    %link{:href => "ico/apple-touch-icon-144-precomposed.png", :rel => "apple-touch-icon-precomposed", :sizes => "144x144"}
    %link{:href => "ico/apple-touch-icon-114-precomposed.png", :rel => "apple-touch-icon-precomposed", :sizes => "114x114"}
    %link{:href => "ico/apple-touch-icon-72-precomposed.png", :rel => "apple-touch-icon-precomposed", :sizes => "72x72"}
    %link{:href => "ico/apple-touch-icon-57-precomposed.png", :rel => "apple-touch-icon-precomposed"}
    %link{:href => "ico/favicon.png", :rel => "shortcut icon"}
  %body
    %div= yield

    %div.row
      %div.col-md-4.col-md-offset-2
        %div.alert.alert-info
          %h4 Information
          %p
            This is Single-Sign-On login page. Please use your Windows username and password. 
            Your user will be locked if you enter a wrong password seven times consecutively. 
            <strong>In case of problems</strong> please contact your sysadmin.
    
      %div.col-md-4
        %div.alert.alert-info
          %h4 Logout
          %p
            In case an integrated application has not adapted its logout URL, you won't logout properly.
            To logout manually, open the URI <code>/oamsso-bin/logout.pl</code>
    
    %div.row
      %div.col-md-8.col-md-offset-2
        %div.alert.alert-info
          %h4 SSO Mechanism
          Single-Sing-On is sitting in front of each integrated application, acting as a gate-keeper
          checking every request if the requested resource (URL) is protected, public (open, but audit
          entry generate), or extcluded (bypass).  If he resource is protected, the requester needs a 
          session, otherwise the authentication flow is started.
          Session are stored in two locations: at server-side and at client-side.  Like most other web 
          apps we use browser cookies at client side.
    
          %h4 Session and time
          Sessions become invalid after 24 h, a new authentication is required
          Closing your browser window, will not end the session or delete the cookie. You can open 
          another window or request a different protected resource without another authentication.
    
          %h4 Multiple Sessions
          In case you work with mutliple browsers (machines) or you delete your cookies: there is a 
          hard limit of eight sessions per user (incl. error message).
 
